{"meta": {"centerNodeId": "taxonomy-species-sylvietta-rufescens", "centerNodeType": "taxonomy", "generatedAt": "2026-05-28T16:28:22", "includedNodeCount": 3, "includedLinkCount": 2, "layoutMode": "precomputed-static"}, "center": {"id": "taxonomy-species-sylvietta-rufescens", "name": "Long-billed crombec", "type": "taxonomy"}, "nodes": [{"id": "taxonomy-species-sylvietta-rufescens", "name": "Long-billed crombec", "latinName": "Sylvietta rufescens", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "Long-billed crombec（Sylvietta rufescens）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如Long-billed crombec。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 1, "x": 237.42, "y": 145.65, "z": 694.64}, {"id": "taxonomy-genus-sylvietta", "name": "Sylvietta", "latinName": "Sylvietta", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "Sylvietta（Sylvietta）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联9种鸟类，如Green crombec、Lemon-bellied crombec、White-browed crombec等9种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 9, "x": 671.73, "y": -115.8, "z": -60.32}, {"id": "bird-long-billed-crombec-192059ea", "name": "Long-billed crombec", "englishName": "Long-billed crombec", "latinName": "Sylvietta rufescens", "type": "bird", "status": "LC", "summary": "The long-billed crombec or Cape crombec (Sylvietta rufescens) is an African warbler. The long-billed crombec breeds in southern Africa from the Democratic Republic of the Congo, Zambia and Tanzania southwards to South Africa. This is a common species in fynbos, open woodland, savannah and dry Acacia scrub. Description The long-billed crombec is a small, nearly tailless bird 12 cm long and weighing around 16 g. Its upperparts are brownish grey-brown, and there is a pale grey supercilium, separated from the whitish throat by a dark eye stripe. The whitish breast shades into the buff belly. The long slightly curved bill is blackish. The sexes are similar, and the juvenile resembles the adult. The call is a variable series of trilled notes including trreee-rriiit trreee-rriiit and a harsh pttt. Behaviour The long-billed crombec's nest is a large, hanging bag of grasses, spider webs, and plant fibres, which is attached to the lower limbs of a tree, often an Acacia. The one to three white eggs are incubated for two weeks to hatching, and the chicks are fed by both parents for another two weeks to fledging. This territorial species is monogamous, pairing for life. This bird is usually seen alone, in pairs, or in family groups as it forages methodically from the bottom to the top of bushes and trees for insects and grass seeds. It will join mixed-species feeding flocks. It moves between trees with a bouncy flight. Conservation status This common species has a large range, with an estimated extent of 4,500,000 km². The population size is believed to be large, and the species is not believed to approach the thresholds for the population decline criterion of the IUCN Red List (i.e. declining more than 30% in ten years or three generations). For these reasons, the species is evaluated as least concern. References Ian Sinclair, Phil Hockey and Warwick Tarboton, SASOL Birds of Southern Africa (Struik 2002) ISBN 1-86872-721-1 External links Long-billed crombec - Species text in The Atlas of Southern African Birds.", "shortSummary": "The long-billed crombec or Cape crombec (Sylvietta rufescens) is an African warbler. The long-billed crombec breeds in southern Africa from…", "locations": ["刚果民主共和国", "赞比亚"], "lat": -3.0, "lng": 24.0, "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/63/Crombec_Longbilled_2011_05_16_09_Alan_Manson_Prieska.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-sylvietta", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-sylvietta-rufescens", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-sylvietta", "species": "taxonomy-species-sylvietta-rufescens"}, "expandable": true, "x": 237.42, "y": 145.65, "z": 695.52}], "links": [{"key": "bird-long-billed-crombec-192059ea__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-sylvietta-rufescens", "source": "bird-long-billed-crombec-192059ea", "target": "taxonomy-species-sylvietta-rufescens", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-sylvietta-rufescens__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-sylvietta", "source": "taxonomy-species-sylvietta-rufescens", "target": "taxonomy-genus-sylvietta", "relation": "belongs_to_genus", "label": "属于属", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 分类字段补充：Long-billed crombec 属于属 Sylvietta。"}]}
